    <title ixia_locid="1">Provisioning Network Interfaces on a Compute Host</title>
    <shortdesc ixia_locid="2">You must configure the network interfaces on a host before you can
        unlock it.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author ixia_locid="3">Jim Owens</author>
        <author ixia_locid="4">Tom Towle</author>
        <author ixia_locid="5">Pedro Sanchez</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context id="context_N1002C_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="180">
            <p ixia_locid="92">Titanium Server automatically creates an Ethernet interface for each
                port it detects on the compute node during software installation. You must manually
                create any required interfaces of other types, including Aggregated Ethernet and
                VLAN, and then edit them to attach them to networks.</p>
            <p ixia_locid="174">For a compute host, you must manually attach interfaces for the
                following networks:</p>
            <ul id="ul_z1k_rrp_dx">
                <li ixia_locid="175">
                    <p ixia_locid="176">data networks</p>
                </li>
                <li ixia_locid="181">
                    <p ixia_locid="182">the infrastructure network, if present</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p ixia_locid="183">You must also configure LAG for any interfaces that use it. For more
                information, see <xref href="jow1426951671346.xml" ixia_locid="830"/>.</p>
            <draft-comment author="rstone" ixia_locid="177">CGTS-2211 adds</draft-comment>
            <p ixia_locid="178">The details for attaching an interface depend on the network
                configuration (for example, whether shared interfaces are used). A simple example is
                provided here for convenience. For more information, see <xref href="jow1426948577755.xml" ixia_locid="179"/>.</p>
            <note id="note_N1006B_N1002C_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="267">
                <p ixia_locid="268">You can use hardware profiles to save a configuration from one host and apply it
                    to others. For more information, see <xref href="jow1404333787693.xml" ixia_locid="269"/>
                </p>
            </note>
        </context>
        <prereq id="prereq_N10066_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="184">
            <p ixia_locid="185">The Titanium Server software must be installed on the host.</p>
            <p ixia_locid="186">To configure the data interfaces on a compute host, provider networks are
                required.</p>
        </prereq>
        <steps id="steps_nvd_tz5_k4">
            <step id="step_N10077_N10073_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="187">
                <cmd ixia_locid="188">Ensure that provider networks are available for the data
                    interfaces. To create them, see <xref href="jow1431018516980.xml" ixia_locid="189"/>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step conref="jow1426453628262.xml#jow1426453628262/step_N1002B_N10028_N1001C_N10001" id="step_N1002B_N10028_N1001C_N10001" ixia_locid="133">
                <cmd ixia_locid="190"/>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10034_N10028_N1001C_N10001" ixia_locid="191">
                <cmd ixia_locid="192">Select the <uicontrol ixia_locid="137">Interfaces</uicontrol>
                    tab.</cmd>
                <stepresult ixia_locid="138">
                    <fig id="fig_ypk_blk_lr" ixia_locid="139">
                        <image href="jow1426954731455.image" id="image_onc_hlk_lr" ixia_locid="140">
                            <alt ixia_locid="141">Compute node default interfaces</alt>
                        </image>
                    </fig>
                </stepresult>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N100B7_N10073_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="193">
                <cmd ixia_locid="77">Configure the data interfaces.</cmd>
                <substeps id="substeps_ufm_yrp_dx">
                    <substep ixia_locid="194">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="195">Click <nameliteral ixia_locid="196">Edit Interface</nameliteral> for a port connected to
                            a data network.</cmd>
                        <info ixia_locid="197">
                            <p ixia_locid="198">The <wintitle ixia_locid="199">Edit
                                    Interface</wintitle> dialog box appears.</p>
                            <fig id="fig_vl5_rvp_dx" ixia_locid="23">
                                <image href="jow1426954976474.image" id="image_wl5_rvp_dx" ixia_locid="24">
                                    <alt ixia_locid="25">TiS Edit Interface</alt>
                                </image>
                            </fig>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep ixia_locid="200">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="201">In the <uicontrol ixia_locid="202">Network Type</uicontrol> list, select
                                <uicontrol ixia_locid="203">data</uicontrol>.</cmd>
                        <info ixia_locid="204">
                            <note id="note_N10101_N100FE_N100EF_N100BE_N100B6_N10073_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="205">
                                <p ixia_locid="206">Ensure that <nameliteral ixia_locid="207">none</nameliteral> is <i ixia_locid="208">not</i>
                                    selected. Clear it if necessary.</p>
                            </note>
                            <p ixia_locid="209">When data is selected, additional controls appear in the dialog box,
                                so that you can select a provider network and enable or disable IPv4
                                and IPv6 addressing modes:</p>
                            <ul id="ul_fqx_4xp_dx">
                                <li ixia_locid="210">
                                    <p ixia_locid="211">a <uicontrol ixia_locid="212">Provider Networks</uicontrol> list</p>
                                </li>
                                <li ixia_locid="213">
                                    <p ixia_locid="214"><uicontrol ixia_locid="215">IPv4 Addressing Mode</uicontrol> options</p>
                                </li>
                                <li ixia_locid="216">
                                    <p ixia_locid="217"><uicontrol ixia_locid="218">IPv6 Addressing Mode</uicontrol> options</p>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep importance="optional" ixia_locid="219">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="220">Specify the <uicontrol ixia_locid="221">Interface
                                Type</uicontrol>.</cmd>
                        <info ixia_locid="222">
                            <p ixia_locid="223">This selection is set to <option ixia_locid="270">Ethernet</option>
                                by default, and is active only if other choices are valid for the
                                configuration. You can select <option ixia_locid="224">Ethernet</option>, <option ixia_locid="225">Aggregated
                                    Ethernet</option>, or <option ixia_locid="226">VLAN</option>.</p>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep ixia_locid="227">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="228">Select a <uicontrol ixia_locid="229">Provider Network</uicontrol> to use with the data
                            interface.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep importance="optional" ixia_locid="230">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="231">Set the <uicontrol ixia_locid="232">IPv4 Addressing
                                Mode</uicontrol> and <uicontrol ixia_locid="233">IPv6 Addressing
                                Mode</uicontrol> for the interface.</cmd>
                        <info ixia_locid="271">
                            <p ixia_locid="272">These selections are active only if the interface is attached to a
                                VXLAN provider network.</p>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep ixia_locid="234">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="235">Click <uicontrol ixia_locid="236">Save</uicontrol> to save the selection and close the
                            dialog box.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N1018B_N10073_N10029_N10001" importance="optional" ixia_locid="237">
                <cmd ixia_locid="238">Configure the infrastructure interface.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="239">
                    <p ixia_locid="240">This step is required only for systems with an optional infrastructure
                        network.</p>
                </info>
                <substeps id="substeps_lkb_lsp_dx">
                    <substep ixia_locid="241">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="242">Click <nameliteral ixia_locid="243">Edit Interface</nameliteral> for the port connected
                            to the infrastructure network.</cmd>
                        <info ixia_locid="244">
                            <p ixia_locid="245">The <wintitle ixia_locid="246">Edit
                                    Interface</wintitle> dialog box appears.</p>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep ixia_locid="247">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="248">In the <uicontrol ixia_locid="249">Network Type</uicontrol> list, select
                                <uicontrol ixia_locid="250">infra</uicontrol>.</cmd>
                        <info ixia_locid="251">
                            <note id="note_N101C9_N101C6_N101B7_N10199_N10189_N10073_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="252">
                                <p ixia_locid="253">Ensure that <nameliteral ixia_locid="254">none</nameliteral> is <i ixia_locid="255">not</i>
                                    selected. Clear it if necessary.</p>
                            </note>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep ixia_locid="256">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="257">Specify the <uicontrol ixia_locid="258">Interface Type</uicontrol>.</cmd>
                        <info ixia_locid="259">
                            <p ixia_locid="260">For an infrastructure interface, you can select an
                                    <option ixia_locid="261">Ethernet</option>, <option ixia_locid="262">Aggregated Ethernet</option>,
                                or <option ixia_locid="263">VLAN interface</option>.</p>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep ixia_locid="264">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="265">Click <uicontrol ixia_locid="266">Save</uicontrol> to save the selection and close the
                            dialog box.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
